File: Bullet JOHANNESBURG - The Gauteng Department of Human Settlements has condemned the killing of a senior official in Ekurhuleni. Teboho Makhoa died in a hail of gunfire on Friday night after 28 bullets were fired at his vehicle. READ: One killed after KZN shooting at ANC councillor's home The department is calling for a quick investigation. According to the department, Makhoa and his colleagues in the Ekurhuleni Regional Office were allocating RDP houses to beneficiaries and removing illegal occupants from invading the land.